    <para id="id9661706">Now we take the limit as Δ→0, k→∞, kΔ=τ, xΔ(t) → x(t), hΔ(t−kΔ) → h(t−τ), and δΔ(t−kΔ) → δ(t−τ) in a generalized function sense. Then the sums approach the integrals</para>
    <para id="id7333337">
      <m:math>
        <m:semantics>
