    <para id="id9551635">V. THE UNIT SAMPLE/IMPULSE RESPONSE</para>
    <para id="id9551640">The unit sample/impulse response of an LTI system characterizes that system. How can we measure this response on a real system? To indicate how this might be done we will determine the impulse response of a CT LTI system that is a lowpass filter.</para>
    <figure id="id9551651">
      <media id="id4304144" alt=""><image src="../../media/graphics14-a728.png" mime-type="image/png" height="154" width="234"/></media>
    </figure>
    <para id="id8604025">To find the impulse response we will determine the response to a tall, narrow, rectangular pulse.</para>
    <para id="id8604031">Two-minute miniquiz problem</para>
    <para id="id8604035">Problem 14-1 — Rectangular pulse response of a LPF</para>
    <para id="id8604041">Determine vo(t) in response to the pulse shown.</para>
    <figure id="id8604072">
      <media id="id4101928" alt=""><image src="../../media/graphics15-de15.png" mime-type="image/png" height="156" width="346"/></media>
    </figure>
    <para id="id8604096">[Hint: use superposition.]</para>
    <para id="id8604100">Solution</para>
    <para id="id8604104">Note that vi(t) can be written as the difference of a step and a step delayed that is scaled as follows</para>
    <para id="id8604134">
      <m:math>
        <m:semantics>
          <m:mrow>
            <m:mstyle fontsize="12pt">
              <m:mrow>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:msub>
                    <m:mi>v</m:mi>
                    <m:mstyle fontsize="8pt">
                      <m:mrow>
                        <m:mi>i</m:mi>
                      </m:mrow>
                    </m:mstyle>
                  </m:msub>
                  <m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo>
                  <m:mi>t</m:mi>
                  <m:mrow>
                    <m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo>
                    <m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo>
                    <m:mfrac>
                      <m:mn>1</m:mn>
                      <m:mi>Δ</m:mi>
                    </m:mfrac>
                  </m:mrow>
                  <m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo>
                  <m:mi>u</m:mi>
                  <m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo>
                  <m:mi>t</m:mi>
                  <m:mrow>
                    <m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo>
                    <m:mo stretchy="false">−</m:mo>
                    <m:mi>u</m:mi>
                  </m:mrow>
                  <m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo>
                  <m:mrow>
                    <m:mi>t</m:mi>
                    <m:mo stretchy="false">−</m:mo>
                    <m:mi>Δ</m:mi>
                  </m:mrow>
                  <m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo>
                  <m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo>
                </m:mrow>
              </m:mrow>
            </m:mstyle>
            <m:mrow/>
          </m:mrow>
          <m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{v rSub { size 8{i} }  \( t \) = {  {1}  over  {Δ} }  \( u \( t \)  - u \( t - Δ \)  \) } {}</m:annotation>
        </m:semantics>
      </m:math>
      <m:math>
        <m:semantics>
          <m:mrow/>
          <m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0">{}</m:annotation>
        </m:semantics>
      </m:math>
    </para>
    <para id="id8604300">Therefore, we need only find the response of the network to a unit step vi(t)=u(t). We denote the step response as vo(t)=s(t) which is</para>
    <para id="id9082033">
      <m:math>
        <m:semantics>
          <m:mrow>
            <m:mstyle fontsize="12pt">
              <m:mrow>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mi>s</m:mi>
                  <m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo>
                  <m:mi>t</m:mi>
                  <m:mrow>
                    <m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo>
                    <m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo>
                    <m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo>
                  </m:mrow>
                  <m:mrow>
                    <m:mn>1</m:mn>
                    <m:mo stretchy="false">−</m:mo>
                    <m:msup>
                      <m:mi>e</m:mi>
                      <m:mstyle fontsize="8pt">
                        <m:mrow>
                          <m:mrow>
                            <m:mo stretchy="false">−</m:mo>
                            <m:mi fontstyle="italic">αt</m:mi>
                          </m:mrow>
                        </m:mrow>
                      </m:mstyle>
                    </m:msup>
                  </m:mrow>
                  <m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo>
                  <m:mi>u</m:mi>
                  <m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo>
                  <m:mi>t</m:mi>
                  <m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo>
                </m:mrow>
              </m:mrow>
            </m:mstyle>
            <m:mrow/>
          </m:mrow>
          <m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{s \( t \) = \( 1 - e rSup { size 8{ - αt} }  \) u \( t \) } {}</m:annotation>
        </m:semantics>
      </m:math>
    </para>
    <para id="id9082144">where α = 1/(RC). Therefore, the response to the pulse is</para>
    <para id="id9082176">
      <m:math>
        <m:semantics>
          <m:mrow>
            <m:mstyle fontsize="12pt">
              <m:mrow>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:msub>
                    <m:mi>v</m:mi>
                    <m:mstyle fontsize="8pt">
                      <m:mrow>
                        <m:mi>ο</m:mi>
                      </m:mrow>
                    </m:mstyle>
                  </m:msub>
                  <m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo>
                  <m:mi>t</m:mi>
                  <m:mrow>
                    <m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo>
                    <m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo>
                    <m:mfrac>
                      <m:mn>1</m:mn>
                      <m:mi>Δ</m:mi>
                    </m:mfrac>
                  </m:mrow>
                  <m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo>
                  <m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo>
                  <m:mrow>
                    <m:mn>1</m:mn>
                    <m:mo stretchy="false">−</m:mo>
                    <m:msup>
                      <m:mi>e</m:mi>
                      <m:mstyle fontsize="8pt">
                        <m:mrow>
                          <m:mrow>
                            <m:mo stretchy="false">−</m:mo>
                            <m:mi fontstyle="italic">αt</m:mi>
                          </m:mrow>
                        </m:mrow>
                      </m:mstyle>
                    </m:msup>
                  </m:mrow>
                  <m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo>
                  <m:mi>u</m:mi>
                  <m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo>
                  <m:mi>t</m:mi>
                  <m:mrow>
                    <m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo>
                    <m:mo stretchy="false">−</m:mo>
                    <m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo>
                  </m:mrow>
                  <m:mrow>
                    <m:mn>1</m:mn>
                    <m:mo stretchy="false">−</m:mo>
                    <m:msup>
                      <m:mi>e</m:mi>
                      <m:mstyle fontsize="8pt">
                        <m:mrow>
                          <m:mrow>
                            <m:mrow>
                              <m:mo stretchy="false">−</m:mo>
                              <m:mi>α</m:mi>
                            </m:mrow>
                            <m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo>
                            <m:mrow>
                              <m:mi>t</m:mi>
                              <m:mo stretchy="false">−</m:mo>
                              <m:mi>Δ</m:mi>
                            </m:mrow>
                            <m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo>
                          </m:mrow>
                        </m:mrow>
                      </m:mstyle>
                    </m:msup>
                  </m:mrow>
                  <m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo>
                  <m:mi>u</m:mi>
